  <h1 align=center class="mt-5" ><strong>Notice of Privacy, Nankö®</strong></h1>
  <h3 align=center class="mt-5 ml-5 mr-5 text-justify">We support our clients and in compliance with the provisions of the Federal Law for the Protection of Personal Data Held by Private Parties, we inform you that the personal, as well as financial data provided by natural or legal persons when hiring or buying Our products and / or services will be used by applying the guidelines, policies and procedures to protect your information.</h3>

  <h1 align=center class="mt-5" ><strong>RESPONSIBLE FOR THE TREATMENT OF YOUR PERSONAL DATA</strong></h1>
  <h3 align=center class="mt-5 ml-5 mr-5 text-justify">We are responsible for the processing of the personal data that have been provided by the Holders to whom they correspond. For the purposes of the provisions of the Federal Law on Protection of Personal Data Held by Private Parties (the "LFPDPPP") and other applicable legislation, this Privacy Notice establishes the terms and conditions under which the treatment is conducted. of the personal data of the Holders.<br> <strong>The Holder states that this Privacy Notice has been made known to him by the Responsible, having read, understood and agreed to the terms set forth in this Privacy Notice; Therefore, you give your consent regarding the processing of your personal data.</strong><br> In the event that the personal data collected includes patrimonial or financial data, by signing the corresponding contract, whether in printed format, or using electronic means and their corresponding processes for the formation of consent, acts that constitute express consent will be carried out. <br> of the owner and who grants their consent for ERIKA CHORES DIAZ to make transfers and / or referrals of data.</h3>


  <h1 align=center class="mt-5" ><strong>CONSENT</strong></h1>
  <h3 align=center class="mt-5 ml-5 mr-5 text-justify">By using our website <strong>"https://www.nanko.com.mx" the Owner agrees to the collection and use of their information as described in this Privacy Notice, which was last updated on December 20, 2020.</strong> We do not sell or provide Your information to any external company, the deliveries of the products requested must be sent within a period of no more than 7 business days, we do not return the products sold. For the request and response of the requests to exercise your ARCO rights, the revocation of your consent and the other rights provided for in the LFPDPPP we offer you the following means:<strong> Email: Soporte@nanko.com.mx</strong>
will respond to the Holder within a maximum period of twenty business days, counted from the date the request was received so that, if it is appropriate, make it effective within fifteen business days after the response is communicated. In all cases, the answer will be given by the same means by which you have submitted your request or, where appropriate, by any other means agreed with the Holder. The afore mentioned terms may be extended in terms of the LFPDPPP.<br>
The personal data collected will be protected by appropriate administrative, technical and physical security measures against damage, loss, alteration, destruction or unauthorized use, access or treatment, in accordance with the provisions of the LFPDPPP and other applicable legislation.<br> Notwithstanding the aforementioned, ERIKA CHORES DIAZ does not guarantee that unauthorized third parties cannot have access to the physical or logical systems of the Holders or the Responsible Party or the electronic documents and files stored in their systems.<br> Consequently, ERIKA CHORES DIAZ will in no way be responsible for any damages that may arise from said unauthorized access. You or your duly accredited legal representative may limit the use or disclosure of your personal data through the same means and procedures provided for the exercise of ARCO Rights.<br>

ERIKA CHORES DIAZ reserves the right to periodically update this Privacy Notice to reflect changes in its information practices. It is the responsibility of the Owner to review the content of the Privacy Notice on the site www.nanko.com.mx or by requesting it to the email address Apoyo@nanko.com.mx. <strong>The Responsible Party will understand that if they do not express otherwise, it means that the Holder has read, understood and agreed to the terms set forth therein, which constitutes their consent to changes and / or updates regarding the processing of their personal data.</strong>
</h3>
  <h1 align=center class="mt-5" ><strong>USE OF INFORMATION</strong></h1>
  <h3 align=center class="mt-5 ml-5 mr-5 text-justify">In general, ERIKA CHORES DIAZ, <strong>"https://www.nanko.com.mx"</strong> collect the necessary personal information from the Owner for your order for products or to respond to your requests about our products and to allow you to use the resources available on our website. Personal information includes, but is not limited to, name, physical address, email address, telephone number and any other information that identifies or, when linked to the above information, can identify you as a specific person, at the same time Visitors to the  <strong>"https://www.nanko.com.mx" site are allowed to register to become a registered user. Registering as a registered user is strictly voluntary. When you log in to the site as a registered user, we keep track of the pages you view in order to tailor your future experience on the site. We may use any personal information to send you information and promotional materials about us. <br>The Owner's contact information can also be used if it is necessary to contact him. Also for the subscription of the contracts corresponding to the products and / or services that you buy or contract </strong>, to evaluate the quality of said products and / or services; in the same way, to comply with the Federal Law for the Prevention and Identification of Operations with Resources of Illicit Origin. Likewise, in order to execute the purchasing management processes (requisition, adjudication, verify commercial references, leasing, sale, monitoring and guarantees); to contact you for requests, suggestions, claims and / or any other request; or to carry out technical update actions of the products and / or services that have been acquired from the supplier.<br> Finally, for activities related to access control and safeguarding of material and human resources within the Responsible's facilities. ONLINE SURVEYS ERIKA CHORES DIAZ, values the opinions and comments of all users of its website "https://www.nanko.com.mx" for which reason we occasionally conduct online or email surveys. Your participation in these surveys is completely optional. Survey participants are anonymous unless otherwise noted in the survey. IP ADDRESSES When you connect to our website, we record your IP addresses and information about the type of operating system (for example, Windows98) and the browser software (for example, Microsoft Internet Explorer) that you are using.<br> This helps us to diagnose problems with our servers and for system administration. Your IP address is also used to collect the pages of our site that you are viewing and aggregated demographic information. LINKS TO OTHER WEBSITES Please note that on our site we have links to other websites that may collect personal information about you. <br>This Privacy Notice does not cover the information practices or policies of those websites. We recommend that you read the privacy policies of all these sites, as their policies may be materially different from our policy.</h3>
  <h1 align=center class="mt-5 mb-5" ><strong>RIGHTS</strong></h1>
  <h3 align=center class="mt-5 ml-5 mr-5 text-justify"><strong>If you consider that your right to the protection of personal data has been harmed by any conduct or omission on the part of ERIKA CHORES DIAZ, or you presume any violation of the legal provisions, you may file your disagreement with the National Institute for Access to Information and Protection of Data (INAI), for more information visit www.inai.org.mx.</strong> </h3>
